      "fastest": true,
      "reverse": false,
      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "const S = readline();\nlet compressed = \"\";\nlet count = 1;\n\nfor (let i = 0; i < S.length; i++) {\n    if (S[i] === S[i + 1]) {\n        count++;\n    } else {\n        compressed += count + S[i];\n        count = 1;\n    }\n}\n\nconsole.log(compressed.length > S.length ? S : compressed);",
      "statement": "In the Intergalactic Data Warehouse, you must compress package IDs before sending them through hyper-space.\n\nTo compress a string, replace each group of consecutive identical digits with the number of occurrences followed by the digit itself.\n\n<<Crucial:>> If the resulting compressed string is strictly longer than the original string, you must return the original one instead.",
